  "texts": [
    "This correlation underscores the inherent inequality in information dissemination across academic journals.",
    "[32] Based on our bibliometric analysis, ZHENG B stands out as the most prolific author, frequently publishing in the field of AI for breast cancer research.",
    "Conversely, KARSSEMEIJER N emerges as one of the most impactful authors, boasting 2133 citations and an H-index of 16.",
    "The work by Hosny A, Parmar C, et al. (2018) addresses the challenges in clinical implementation and provides insights on advancing the domain, making it the most globally cited and influential article in AI for breast cancer diagnosis and prognosis research from 2000 to 2024.",
